              <h3 class="next-step__title">Per-Member Authentication</h3>
              <p class="next-step__text">Currently all household members share one auth session. The next step is giving each member their own Supabase identity so they sign in individually, with the household model linking their accounts.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="next-step">
              <h3 class="next-step__title">Screen Reader Testing</h3>
              <p class="next-step__text">Conduct hands-on testing with NVDA, JAWS, and VoiceOver — particularly for the cloud version's new modals (share, Plaid mapping, account switching) and the multi-column side-by-side view.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="next-step">
              <h3 class="next-step__title">Offline Sync &amp; Mobile App</h3>
              <p class="next-step__text">Add service worker + IndexedDB support so the cloud version works offline, then explore React Native to bring the household budget to mobile devices.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

